<p class="p">First, we used the modified method described by 
 <xref rid="ref-19" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">Calabrese et al. (2014)</xref> to compute the climatic suitability of multi-IPS in each pixel: 
 <disp-formula id="eqn-1" class="disp-formula">
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <graphic xlink:href="peerj-07-6479-e001.jpg" mimetype="image" mime-subtype="png" position="float" orientation="portrait" class="graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   <tex-math id="M1" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{upgreek} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document} }{}$${E_j} = \sum\limits_{i = k}^k {{P_{i,j}}} $$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <math id="mml-eqn-1" class="math">
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <msub class="msub">
      <mi class="mi">E</mi>
      <mi class="mi">j</mi>
     </msub>
     <mo class="mo">=</mo>
     <mstyle displaystyle="true" class="mstyle">
      <munderover class="munderover">
       <mo class="mo">âˆ‘</mo>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi class="mi">i</mi>
        <mo class="mo">=</mo>
        <mi class="mi">k</mi>
       </mrow>
       <mi class="mi">k</mi>
      </munderover>
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <msub class="msub">
        <mi class="mi">P</mi>
        <mrow class="mrow">
         <mi class="mi">i</mi>
         <mo class="mo">,</mo>
         <mi class="mi">j</mi>
        </mrow>
       </msub>
      </mrow>
     </mstyle>
    </mrow>
   </math>
  </alternatives>
 </disp-formula> where 
 <italic class="italic">E
  <sub class="sub">j</sub>
 </italic> represents the current or future climatic suitability of multi-IPS in pixel 
 <italic class="italic">j</italic>; 
 <italic class="italic">k</italic> is the number of IPS in pixel 
 <italic class="italic">j</italic>; and 
 <italic class="italic">P
  <sub class="sub">i</sub>,
  <sub class="sub">j</sub>
 </italic> is the climatic suitability of multi-IPS in pixel 
 <italic class="italic">j</italic>.
</p>
